Mathematical Beauty

Archimedean Spiral

\[x=(\alpha+\beta\theta)\cos\theta\] \[y=(\alpha+\beta\theta)\sin\theta\] Take \(\alpha=0\) and \(\beta=1\)

Logarithmic Spirals

\[x=\alpha e^{\beta\theta}\cos\theta\] \[y=\alpha e^{\beta\theta}\sin\theta\] Take \(\alpha=0.1\) and \(\beta=0.1\)

A special case: when \(\beta\approx0.3063489\), the spiral is called a Golden Spiral.

Limaçon de Pascal

\[x=(\alpha+\beta\cos\theta)\cos\theta\] \[y=(\alpha+\beta\cos\theta)\sin\theta\] Take \(\alpha=0.5\) and \(\beta=1\)

Heart Curve

\[x=\alpha(1-\sin\theta)\cos\theta\] \[y=\alpha(1-\sin\theta)\sin\theta\] Take \(\alpha=1\)

\[x=\arccos(\sin\theta)\cdot\cos\theta\] \[y=\arccos(\sin\theta)\cdot\sin\theta\]

Rose Curve

\[x=\cos n\theta\cdot\cos\theta\] \[y=\cos n\theta\cdot\sin\theta\] Take \(n=\frac{2}{3}\)

Take \(n=\frac{1}{4}\)

Take \(n=\frac{3}{4}\)

Take \(n=\frac{2}{5}\)

Take \(n=\frac{3}{5}\)

Take \(n=e\)

Take \(n=\pi\)

Take \(n=\sqrt{2}\)
